song_name: Down In The Ground Where The Dead Men Go

version_description: This is a simple 5 chord version with Capo on 2,easily played on acoustic guitar,i have included Intro,Links and instrumental break ,Although this was written by the pogues it is famous for featuring Kirsty MacColl,one of the best Christmas songs ever written.

Capo on 4th or 2nd (what ever suits you personally). To make it sound better (although you dont have to do this atall) keep your pinky and ring finger pressed down on the bottom 2 strings in the 3rd fret for the whole song. When playing the first D chord of verses 1, 2 and 6, play the first 4 beats of the chord with all fingers down, but for the second 4 beats lift your pinky finger off the bottom strings. As soon as you go into the G in the next line hold down on your pinky again.
I've included a guitar tab for the piano intro in the original.
altered a previous tab to put chords on the wholes song to make it easier
